<h2>Solar Incentives in Atlanta</h2>
<p>Atlanta homeowners benefit from the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC), which provides a 30% tax credit on the total cost of solar panel installation through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Georgia offers additional incentives including a state tax credit of up to \$2,500 for solar installations, though this program has limited funding and operates on a first-come, first-served basis. Georgia Power also provides rebates for solar installations through their Advanced Solar Initiative, offering payments for solar energy systems that connect to their grid. Property tax exemptions are available in Georgia, meaning the added value of solar panels to your home won't increase your property taxes. Additionally, sales tax exemptions apply to solar equipment purchases, saving Atlanta residents the 7% state sales tax plus local taxes on their solar investment.</p>

