<p>When selecting a solar installer in Atlanta, look for companies with proper Georgia licensing, including electrical contractor licenses and solar-specific certifications from organizations like NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners). Experienced local installers understand Atlanta's building codes, permitting processes, and Georgia Power's interconnection requirements. Top-rated companies should offer comprehensive warranties including 20-25 year panel warranties, 10+ year inverter warranties, and workmanship guarantees of at least 10 years. Check for BBB accreditation, positive customer reviews on platforms like Google and Angie's List, and ask for local references from recent Atlanta installations. Reputable installers will provide detailed site assessments, multiple financing options, handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork, and offer ongoing monitoring and maintenance services to ensure optimal system performance throughout Atlanta's varying weather conditions.</p>

